    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect loop bounds in RRC NGAP PDU session handling\n\n### Summary\nIncorrect loop bounds and array indexing in RRC NGAP PDU session handling functions can cause buffer overflows and incorrect behavior when processing PDU session modify and release commands.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB_NGAP.c`: Fixed multiple instances of incorrect array indexing and missing bounds checking in PDU session processing functions.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen a UE with many PDU sessions receives a PDU session modify request for a non-existing session, the code incorrectly accesses memory beyond the allocated PDU session array, leading to potential crashes or data corruption. Similarly, when processing PDU session release commands for non-existing sessions, buffer overflows can occur due to missing bounds checks before incrementing the session count.\n\nSymptoms include:\n- Segmentation faults during PDU session management\n- Incorrect PDU session state handling\n- Potential memory corruption in UE context data\n"
}